name: user-provider-application
description: The User Provider Application, developed with Java 17 and Spring Boot, is a critical microservice responsible for managing user data. This microservice handles all user-related activities, including profiles, settings, and follow-following functionalities. It is essential for maintaining comprehensive and user management within the system.

name: microservices-python
description: microservices architecture and distributed systems using Python, Kubernetes, RabbitMQ, MongoDB, and MySQL.

name: iface-ml-service
description: Machine Learning microservice for Iface system

name: software_projects
description: Microservices for a software projects management system

name: trafic-toll-calculator
description: A microservices-based system designed to calculate traffic tolls for trucks, with potential applications in broader logistics operations. The system leverages modern technologies to ensure scalability, efficiency, and real-time processing.

name: goffee-shop
description: goffee-shop is a food and beverage ordering application used in cafes and fast-food stores. Technically, the system consists of microservices written in Golang.

name: Payment-Processing-Service
description: This project involves developing a core payment system for an e-commerce client using Stripe payment gateway integration. The project is built using Java and Spring Boot, utilizing microservices architecture, and is hosted on AWS. It focuses on providing a reliable, scalable, and secure payment processing system.

name: personalized-recommendation-engine
description: This is a microservice-based application designed to track user behavior and provide personalized recommendations based on that behavior. The application leverages a combination of Golang, Flask, and Kafka to deliver a scalable and efficient recommendation system.

name: EurekaServer
description: EurekaServer is a service registry for microservices to register and discover each other within a distributed system. Part of the Spring Cloud ecosystem and Netflix OSS stack, it simplifies service management and scaling by providing dynamic service registration, discovery, and fault tolerance.
